<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-12497] COPY ... TO STDOUT regression in 2.2.7</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-12497</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Cassandra 2.2.7 introduces a regression over 2.2.6 breaking COPY ... TO STDOUT.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In pylib/cqlshlib/copyutil.py, in CopyTask._&lt;em&gt;init&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;, self.printmsg is conditionally defined to EITHER a module level function accepting arguments (msg, eol=, encoding=), OR a lambda accepting arguments only (&lt;/em&gt;, eol=).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Consequently, when the lambda is in use (which requires COPY ... TO STDOUT without --debug), any attempt to call CopyTask.printmsg with an encoding parameter causes an exception.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This occurs in ExportTask.run, thus rendering all COPY ... TO STDOUT without --debug broken.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is to update the lambda&apos;s arguments to include encoding, or better, replace it with a module-level function defined next to printmsg, so that people realize the two argument lists must be kept in sync.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The regression was introduced in this commit:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;commit 5de9de1f5832f2a0e92783e2f4412874423e6e15&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Tyler Hobbs &amp;lt;tylerlhobbs@gmail.com&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   Thu May 5 11:33:35 2016 -0500&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    cqlsh: Handle non-ascii chars in error messages&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Patch by Tyler Hobbs; reviewed by Paulo Motta for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-11626&quot; title=&quot;cqlsh fails and exits on non-ascii chars&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-11626&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-11626&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
